  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***signal phrase*** is the clause that introduces a quotation, [paraphrase](./paraphrase.md), or summary and attributes it to its source. \"As Smith argues,\" \"According to the report,\" \"Ogilvy claimed that\" — these are signal phrases. They tell the reader who is speaking before the reader encounters the idea.",
